verses.verse: Praise <WH8416> waits <WH1747> for you, <WH430> God, in Zion. <WH6726> To you shall vows <WH5088> be performed. <WH7999>
You who hear <WH8085> prayer, <WH8605> to you all men <WH1320> will come. <WH935>
Sins <WH1697> overwhelmed <WH1396> me, <WH3722> but you atoned for our transgressions. <WH6588>

Blessed <WH835> is one whom you choose, <WH977> and cause to come near, <WH7126> that he may live <WH7931> in your courts. <WH2691> We will be filled <WH7646> with the goodness <WH2898> of your house, <WH1004> your holy <WH6918> temple. <WH1964>

By awesome deeds <WH3372> of righteousness, <WH6664> you answer <WH6030> us, <WH430> God of our salvation. <WH3468> You who are the hope <WH4009> of all the ends <WH7099> of the earth, <WH776> of those who are far away <WH7350> on the sea; <WH3220>
Who by his power <WH3581> forms <WH3559> the mountains, <WH2022> having armed <WH247> yourself with strength; <WH1369>
who stills <WH7623> the roaring <WH7588> of the seas, <WH3220> the roaring <WH7588> of their waves, <WH1530> and the turmoil <WH1995> of the nations. <WH3816>
They also who dwell <WH3427> in faraway places <WH7099> are afraid <WH3372> at your wonders. <WH226> You call the morning <WH1242>'s dawn <WH1242> and the evening <WH6153> with songs of joy. <WH7442>

You visit <WH6485> the earth, <WH776> and water <WH7783> it. <WH7227> You greatly enrich <WH6238> it. <WH6388> The river of God <WH430> is full <WH4390> of water. <WH4325> You provide <WH3559> them grain, <WH1715> for so you have ordained it. <WH3559>
You drench <WH7301> its <WH7301> furrows. <WH1417> You level <WH5181> its ridges. <WH8525> You soften <WH4127> it with showers. <WH7241> You bless <WH1288> it with a crop. <WH6780>
You crown <WH5849> the year <WH8141> with your bounty. <WH2896> Your carts <WH4570> overflow <WH7491> with abundance. <WH1880>
The wilderness <WH4057> grasslands <WH4999> overflow. <WH7491> The hills <WH1389> are clothed <WH2296> with gladness. <WH1524>
The pastures <WH3733> are covered <WH3847> with flocks. <WH6629> The valleys <WH6010> also are clothed <WH5848> with grain. <WH1250> They shout for joy! <WH7321> They also sing. <WH7891>
